{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866209293,"sessionID":"ses_2862337a6ffeds16ehO2RvNRjD","part":{"id":"prt_d79dfdfd2001l16VFqyGa3jLRp","messageID":"msg_d79dfc27a001DPZssDnQMk8wE0","sessionID":"ses_2862337a6ffeds16ehO2RvNRjD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_171864c0c2fc4f78aacf44d0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-027 вҖ” SDK CodeInterpreterClient вҖ” Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** sdk-python\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-027/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-027/design.md`, `changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md`\n8: > **Dependency:** None\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## T-1: Package scaffolding and configuration\n13: \n14: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/pyproject.toml` with package name `agentcube-sdk`, Python >=3.10, dependencies (`requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`)\n15: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/__init__.py` with `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n16: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with `__all__ = [\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n17: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/__init__.py` as empty module marker\n18: - [ ] Write test: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` succeeds\n19: - [ ] Write test: `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` succeeds\n20: - [ ] Write test: `agentcube.__all__` contains exactly `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n21: - [ ] Write test: `agentcube.clients.__all__` contains exactly `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n22: \n23: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_import\"`\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## T-2: Exception hierarchy\n28: \n29: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n30: - [ ] Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)` as base class with docstring\n31: - [ ] Define `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)` with `__init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None)` and message format `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n32: - [ ] Define `SessionError(AgentCubeError)` with docstring `\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"`\n33: - [ ] Define `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)` with docstring `\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"`\n34: - [ ] Export all exceptions from `agentcube.exceptions`\n35: - [ ] Write test: `CommandExecutionError` has `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` attributes\n36: - [ ] Write test: `CommandExecutionError` message includes exit code and stderr\n37: - [ ] Write test: all custom exceptions are catchable as `AgentCubeError`\n38: - [ ] Write test: `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` have correct docstrings\n39: \n40: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_exception\"`\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## T-3: Utility helpers (http, utils, log)\n45: \n46: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/http.py` with `create_session()` helper\n47: - [ ] Implement `create_session()` to return `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` mounted for `http://` and `https://`\n48: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/utils.py` with `read_token_from_file(path)` helper\n49: - [ ] Implement `read_token_from_file(path)` to read file content and strip whitespace; return `\"\"` if file does not exist\n50: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/log.py` with `get_logger(name, verbose=False)` helper\n51: - [ ] Implement `get_logger()` to set level to `DEBUG` if `verbose=True`, else `INFO`\n52: - [ ] Write test: `create_session()` returns session with correct adapter config\n53: - [ ] Write test: `read_token_from_file()` returns token content when file exists\n54: - [ ] Write test: `read_token_from_file()` returns `\"\"` when file does not exist\n55: - [ ] Write test: `get_logger(verbose=True)` sets DEBUG level\n56: - [ ] Write test: `get_logger(verbose=False)` sets INFO level\n57: \n58: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_utils\"`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## T-4: ControlPlaneClient\n63: \n64: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n65: - [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__(self, workload_manager_url=None, auth_token=None, timeout=None, verbose=False)`\n66: - [ ] Resolve `workload_manager_url` from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var; raise `ValueError` if neither provided\n67: - [ ] Resolve `auth_token`: use arg, or read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, or `\"\"`\n68: - [ ] Create session via `create_session()` with default headers `Content-Type: application/json` and `Authorization: Bearer {token}` if token is non-empty\n69: - [ ] Set default timeout tuple `(5.0, 120)` if not provided\n70: - [ ] Implement `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)` вҶ’ POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{name, namespace, ttl, metadata}`, return session ID from response\n71: - [ ] Implement `delete_session(session_id)` вҶ’ DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`, return bool\n72: - [ ] Implement `close()` to close the session\n73: - [ ] Write test: constructor with explicit `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token`\n74: - [ ] Write test: constructor resolves `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` from env var\n75: - [ ] Write test: constructor raises `ValueError` when no URL provided\n76: - [ ] Write test: auth token from service account file when file exists\n77: - [ ] Write test: auth token empty when SA file missing\n78: - [ ] Write test: `create_session` POSTs correct body and returns session ID\n79: - [ ] Write test: `delete_session` DELETEs correct URL and returns bool\n80: - [ ] Write test: `close()` closes session without error\n81: \n82: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_control_plane\"`\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## T-5: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n87: \n88: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n89: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__(self, session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name, base_url=None, timeout=None, verbose=False)`\n90: - [ ] Construct `base_url` via `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` if not provided\n91: - [ ] Create session via `create_session()` with default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (lowercase)\n92: - [ ] Set default timeout tuple `(5.0, 120)` if not provided\n93: - [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` вҶ’ POST `api/execute` with body `{\"command\": command, \"timeout\": \"{timeout}s\"}`, return stdout from response\n94: - [ ] Implement `write_file(content, remote_path)` вҶ’ POST `api/files` with JSON body `{\"path\": remote_path, \"content\": <base64-encoded>, \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n95: - [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` вҶ’ POST multipart to `api/files` with `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path': remote_path, 'mode': '0644'}`\n96: - [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` вҶ’ GET `api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` (where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`), write response content to `local_path`\n97: - [ ] Implement `list_files(path=\".\")` вҶ’ GET `api/files` with query parameter `path={path}`, return response\n98: - [ ] Implement `close()` to close the session\n99: - [ ] Write test: constructor constructs `base_url` from `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name`\n100: - [ ] Write test: constructor uses explicit `base_url` when provided\n101: - [ ] Write test: session has `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n102: - [ ] Write test: `execute_command` POSTs correct body with default timeout `120s`\n103: - [ ] Write test: `execute_command` POSTs correct body with custom timeout\n104: - [ ] Write test: `write_file` POSTs JSON with base64-encoded content\n105: - [ ] Write test: `upload_file` POSTs multipart with correct fields\n106: - [ ] Write test: `download_file` GETs with stream and writes to local path\n107: - [ ] Write test: `list_files` GETs with query param `path=.`\n108: - [ ] Write test: `list_files` GETs with query param `path=/tmp`\n109: - [ ] Write test: `close()` closes session without error\n110: \n111: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane\"`\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ## T-6: CodeInterpreterClient initialization and session lifecycle\n116: \n117: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n118: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__(self, name=\"my-interpreter\", namespace=\"default\", ttl=3600, workload_manager_url=None, router_url=None, auth_token=None, verbose=False, session_id=None)`\n119: - [ ] Resolve `router_url` from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var; raise `ValueError` if neither provided\n120: - [ ] Initialize `cp_client` (ControlPlaneClient) with `workload_manager_url`, `auth_token`, `timeout=(5.0, 120)`, `verbose`\n121: - [ ] If `session_id` not provided, call `cp_client.create_session(name, namespace, ttl=ttl)` and store returned session ID\n122: - [ ] If `session_id` provided, use it directly without calling `create_session`\n123: - [ ] Call `_init_data_plane()` to initialize `dp_client`\n124: - [ ] Implement `_init_data_plane()`: construct `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id`, `router_url`, `namespace`, `cr_name=name`\n125: - [ ] Implement data plane init failure rollback: if `session_id` was created (not provided) and `_init_data_plane()` raises, log warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise\n126: - [ ] If `session_id` was provided and `_init_data_plane()` raises, do NOT delete session, just re-raise\n127: - [ ] Write test: constructor with all defaults uses env `ROUTER_URL`\n128: - [ ] Write test: constructor raises `ValueError` when no `router_url` arg or env var\n129: - [ ] Write test: constructor with explicit config sets all fields correctly\n130: - [ ] Write test: session creation on init when `session_id` not provided\n131: - [ ] Write test: session reuse when `session_id` is provided (no `create_session` call)\n132: - [ ] Write test: data plane init failure with created session triggers rollback (delete + re-raise)\n133: - [ ] Write test: data plane init failure with provided session does NOT delete session\n134: \n135: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_code_interpreter_init\"`\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## T-7: CodeInterpreterClient context manager and stop\n140: \n141: - [ ] Implement `__enter__()` to return `self`\n142: - [ ] Implement `__exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)` to call `stop()` and return `None` (do not suppress exceptions)\n143: - [ ] Implement `stop()` to close `dp_client`, delete control plane session if `session_id` is set, close `cp_client`\n144: - [ ] Implement `stop()` idempotency: safe to call multiple times without errors\n145: - [ ] Write test: `__enter__` returns `self`\n146: - [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with no exception calls `stop()`\n147: - [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with exception calls `stop()` and does not suppress exception\n148: - [ ] Write test: `stop()` closes dp_client, deletes session, closes cp_client\n149: - [ ] Write test: `stop()` called twice does not raise error\n150: \n151: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_context_manager or test_stop\"`\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## T-8: CodeInterpreterClient command execution\n156: \n157: - [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None)` on `CodeInterpreterClient`\n158: - [ ] If `command` is a string, convert to list `[command]`\n159: - [ ] Default timeout to `120` if not provided\n160: - [ ] Call `dp_client.execute_command(command, timeout=timeout)` with HTTP read timeout = `timeout + 2.0` buffer\n161: - [ ] Parse response: if `exit_code != 0`, raise `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)`\n162: - [ ] Return stdout from response\n163: - [ ] Write test: `execute_command(\"echo hello\")` POSTs with body `{\"command\": [\"echo hello\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` and returns stdout\n164: - [ ] Write test: `execute_command` with `timeout=30.0` sends `\"timeout\": \"30s\"` and HTTP read timeout is `32.0`\n165: - [ ] Write test: `execute_command` with `timeout=None` defaults to `120s` and HTTP read timeout is `122.0`\n166: - [ ] Write test: `execute_command` with list `[\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hi')\"]` sends list in body\n167: - [ ] Write test: response with `exit_code != 0` raises `CommandExecutionError` with correct attributes\n168: \n169: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_execute_command\"`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## T-9: CodeInterpreterClient code execution\n174: \n175: - [ ] Implement `run_code(language, code, timeout=None)` on `CodeInterpreterClient`\n176: - [ ] Support language aliases: `python`, `python3`, `py` вҶ’ write `.py` file and execute `python3 <file>`\n177: - [ ] Generate timestamped filename (e.g., `/tmp/code_{timestamp}.py`)\n178: - [ ] Call `write_file(content, remote_path)` to write code to remote file\n179: - [ ] Call `execute_command(f\"python3 {remote_path}\", timeout=timeout)` to run\n180: - [ ] Raise `ValueError` for unsupported languages\n181: - [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"python\", code=\"print('hi')\")` writes `.py` file and executes `python3 <file>`\n182: - [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"python3\", ...)` treated as Python\n183: - [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"py\", ...)` treated as Python\n184: - [ ] Write test: `run_code(language=\"java\", ...)` raises `ValueError` for unsupported language\n185: \n186: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_run_code\"`\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## T-10: CodeInterpreterClient file operations\n191: \n192: - [ ] Implement `write_file(content, remote_path)` вҶ’ delegate to `dp_client.write_file(content, remote_path)`\n193: - [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` вҶ’ delegate to `dp_client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n194: - [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` вҶ’ delegate to `dp_client.download_file(remote_path, local_path)`\n195: - [ ] Implement `list_files(path=\".\")` вҶ’ delegate to `dp_client.list_files(path)`\n196: - [ ] Write test: `write_file` delegates to dp_client with correct args\n197: - [ ] Write test: `upload_file` delegates to dp_client with correct args\n198: - [ ] Write test: `download_file` delegates to dp_client with correct args\n199: - [ ] Write test: `list_files` delegates to dp_client with default path `.`\n200: - [ ] Write test: `list_files` delegates to dp_client with custom path `/tmp`\n201: \n202: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_file_ops\"`\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ## T-11: AgentRuntimeClient stub\n207: \n208: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n209: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class skeleton with `__init__` and docstring\n210: - [ ] Write test: `AgentRuntimeClient` can be imported and instantiated\n211: \n212: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_agent_runtime_stub\"`\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## T-12: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient stub\n217: \n218: - [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n219: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class skeleton with `__init__` and docstring\n220: - [ ] Write test: `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` can be imported and instantiated\n221: \n222: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_agent_runtime_data_plane_stub\"`\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## T-13: Logging configuration\n227: \n228: - [ ] Integrate `get_logger()` into `CodeInterpreterClient` constructor based on `verbose` parameter\n229: - [ ] Add debug-level logging for session creation, data plane init, command execution, file operations\n230: - [ ] Add warning-level logging for data plane init failure rollback\n231: - [ ] Write test: `verbose=True` enables debug logging\n232: - [ ] Write test: `verbose=False` sets INFO level (no debug output)\n233: \n234: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_logging\"`\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## T-14: Integration tests\n239: \n240: - [ ] Write integration test: full session lifecycle with context manager (create вҶ’ execute вҶ’ cleanup)\n241: - [ ] Write integration test: command execution with mocked data plane (mock `requests.Session`)\n242: - [ ] Write integration test: file upload/download with mocked data plane\n243: - [ ] Write integration test: session reuse with provided `session_id`\n244: - [ ] Write integration test: data plane init failure triggers session cleanup\n245: \n246: **Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_integration\"`\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## T-15: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n251: \n252: - [ ] `ruff check python-sdk/agentcube/` вҖ” no violations\n253: - [ ] `mypy python-sdk/agentcube/` вҖ” no type errors\n254: - [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` вҖ” all pass\n255: - [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` вҖ” coverage вүҘ 80%\n256: \n257: **Verification:** Run all lint/typecheck/coverage commands\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Dependency Graph\n262: \n263: ```\n264: T-1  в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-2 в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-4 в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-6 в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-7\n265:        в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ         в”ңв”Җв”Җ T-8\n266:        в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ         в”ңв”Җв”Җ T-9\n267:        в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ         в””в”Җв”Җ T-10\n268:        в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ\n269:        в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ         в””в”Җв”Җ T-5 в”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n270:        в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ\n271:        в”Ӯ          в””в”Җв”Җ T-3 в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-4\n272:        в”Ӯ                    в”ңв”Җв”Җ T-5\n273:        в”Ӯ                    в””в”Җв”Җ T-13\n274:        в”Ӯ\n275:        в””в”Җв”Җ T-11 (stub, parallel)\n276:        \n277: T-12 (stub, parallel with T-11)\n278: \n279: T-14 в”Җв”Җ (T-6, T-7, T-8, T-9, T-10)\n280: \n281: T-15 в”Җв”Җ (all above)\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ## Parallelizable Groups\n285: \n286: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n287: |-------|-------|---------------|\n288: | G1 | T-1 | None |\n289: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-11, T-12 | T-1 |\n290: | G3 | T-4, T-5 | T-2, T-3 |\n291: | G4 | T-6 | T-4, T-5 |\n292: | G5 | T-7, T-8, T-9, T-10, T-13 | T-6 |\n293: | G6 | T-14 | T-7, T-8, T-9, T-10 |\n294: | G7 | T-15 | All above |\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ## Acceptance Criteria\n299: \n300: | # | Criterion | Command |\n301: |---|-----------|---------|\n302: | AC1 | `CodeInterpreterClient` can be imported from `agentcube` | `python -c \"from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\"` |\n303: | AC2 | Context manager lifecycle works (create вҶ’ use вҶ’ cleanup) | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_context_manager\"` |\n304: | AC3 | Command execution with timeout and error handling works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_execute_command\"` |\n305: | AC4 | Code execution supports python/python3/py aliases | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_run_code\"` |\n306: | AC5 | File operations (write, upload, download, list) work | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_file_ops\"` |\n307: | AC6 | Exception hierarchy is correct and catchable | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_exception\"` |\n308: | AC7 | Session reuse with provided `session_id` works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_session_reuse\"` |\n309: | AC8 | Data plane init failure triggers rollback | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_rollback\"` |\n310: | AC9 | Logging respects `verbose` flag | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_logging\"` |\n311: | AC10 | Coverage вүҘ 80% | `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` |\n\n(End of file - total 311 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-027 вҖ” SDK CodeInterpreterClient вҖ” Tasks\n\n> **Module:** sdk-python\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-027/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-027/design.md`, `changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n---\n\n## T-1: Package scaffolding and configuration\n\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/pyproject.toml` with package name `agentcube-sdk`, Python >=3.10, dependencies (`requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`)\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/__init__.py` with `__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with `__all__ = [\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n- [ ] Create `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/__init__.py` as empty module marker\n- [ ] Write test: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient` succeeds\n- [ ] Write test: `from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` succeeds\n- [ ] Write test: `agentcube.__all__` contains exactly `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-027/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775866209280,"end":1775866209290}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866210540,"sessionID":"ses_2862337a6ffeds16ehO2RvNRjD","part":{"id":"prt_d79dfe481001irAH4sHCjpogYG","messageID":"msg_d79dfc27a001DPZssDnQMk8wE0","sessionID":"ses_2862337a6ffeds16ehO2RvNRjD","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_627fd5a864cd4ddf9c2c98f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n13: \n14: The system SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, bootstraps a session ID via the data plane, and initializes the underlying `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Constructor with all arguments\n17: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with explicit `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`\n18: - **WHEN** the constructor completes\n19: - **THEN** all instance fields (`agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`) SHALL be set to the provided values\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Constructor with defaults\n22: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with only `agent_name`\n23: - **WHEN** the constructor completes\n24: - **THEN** `namespace` SHALL default to `\"default\"`, `verbose` to `False`, `session_id` to `None`, `timeout` to `120`, and `connect_timeout` to `5.0`\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n27: - **GIVEN** `router_url` is not provided as an argument\n28: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n29: - **THEN** it SHALL read `router_url` from the `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n32: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n33: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n34: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Data plane client initialization\n37: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n38: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`, storing it as `self.dp_client`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Session ID bootstrapping when not provided\n42: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy\n43: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n44: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` and assign the returned value to `self.session_id`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID missing header\n47: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n48: - **WHEN** `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n49: - **AND** the response does not contain the `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n50: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Session ID reuse when provided\n53: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is provided to the constructor\n54: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT call `bootstrap_session_id()` and SHALL use the provided `session_id` directly\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n58: \n59: The system SHALL support context manager protocol for `AgentRuntimeClient` to ensure proper resource cleanup on block exit.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Context manager entry\n62: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used in a `with` statement\n63: - **WHEN** `__enter__` is called\n64: - **THEN** it SHALL return `self`\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with normal flow\n67: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager and the block completes without exception\n68: - **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with `exc_type=None`\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL call `close()` to clean up resources\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n72: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager and an exception occurs in the block\n73: - **WHEN** `__exit__` is called with exception info\n74: - **THEN** it SHALL call `close()` and SHALL NOT suppress the exception (return `None` or `False`)\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: Invoke Payload\n77: \n78: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` method to send JSON payloads to the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint and return the response.\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Successful invocation\n81: - **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` is set on the client\n82: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called with a dictionary payload\n83: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.invoke(session_id, payload)` and return the `requests.Response` object\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Invoke without session ID\n86: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or falsy on the client\n87: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n88: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n91: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is valid\n92: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=30.0)` is called\n93: - **THEN** the data plane invoke SHALL use `timeout=30.0` for the request\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Invoke with default timeout\n96: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is valid and `timeout` argument is `None`\n97: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload)` is called\n98: - **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Invoke response handling\n101: - **GIVEN** a successful data plane response\n102: - **WHEN** `invoke` receives the response\n103: - **THEN** it SHALL return the response object without parsing (caller is responsible for JSON deserialization)\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Close and Cleanup\n106: \n107: The system SHALL provide a `close` method to release the underlying HTTP session resources.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Close data plane session\n110: - **GIVEN** an initialized `AgentRuntimeClient` with a `dp_client`\n111: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n112: - **THEN** it SHALL call `dp_client.close()` to close the underlying `requests.Session`\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Close without initialized data plane\n115: - **GIVEN** `dp_client` is `None` or not set\n116: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n117: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT raise an exception (no-op or safe guard)\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Close idempotency\n120: - **GIVEN** `close()` is called multiple times\n121: - **WHEN** subsequent calls execute\n122: - **THEN** they SHALL NOT raise errors (safe to call repeatedly)\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Bootstrap\n125: \n126: The system SHALL bootstrap a session ID by sending a GET request to the invocation base URL and reading the response header.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session ID via GET\n129: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` instance\n130: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n131: - **THEN** it SHALL send `GET` to `self.base_url` and read the `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Bootstrap returns session ID\n134: - **GIVEN** the GET response contains header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123`\n135: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` parses the response\n136: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Bootstrap missing session header\n139: - **GIVEN** the GET response does not contain `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n140: - **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` processes the response\n141: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")`\n142: \n143: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Invoke\n144: \n145: The system SHALL send POST requests to the invocation base URL with session headers and JSON payload.\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Invoke via POST\n148: - **GIVEN** a valid `session_id` and `payload`\n149: - **WHEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n150: - **THEN** it SHALL send `POST` to `self.base_url` with headers `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`, and body as JSON-serialized `payload`\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n153: - **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=None`\n154: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n155: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` tuple\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Invoke with explicit timeout\n158: - **GIVEN** `invoke` is called with `timeout=60.0`\n159: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n160: - **THEN** the timeout SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 60.0)` tuple\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Invoke response return\n163: - **GIVEN** the POST request completes\n164: - **WHEN** `invoke` finishes\n165: - **THEN** it SHALL return the `requests.Response` object without parsing\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Base URL\n168: \n169: The system SHALL construct the invocation base URL from router URL, namespace, and agent name.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Base URL construction\n172: - **GIVEN** `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n173: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` initializes\n174: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n175: \n176: ### Requirement: Session Header Management\n177: \n178: The system SHALL use the session header `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Agent Runtime data plane requests.\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Session header constant\n181: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n182: - **WHEN** accessing `SESSION_HEADER`\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Session header on invoke request\n186: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id, payload)` is called\n187: - **WHEN** the POST request is constructed\n188: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Session header on bootstrap GET\n191: - **GIVEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n192: - **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n193: - **THEN** the request SHALL use the session default headers only (no explicit session header needed for bootstrap)\n194: \n195: ### Requirement: HTTP Client Configuration\n196: \n197: The system SHALL configure the HTTP client with appropriate connection pooling and timeout defaults.\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Data plane session configuration\n200: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized\n201: - **WHEN** the session is created\n202: - **THEN** it SHALL have `HTTPAdapter` mounted with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Default timeouts\n205: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n206: - **WHEN** any request is made\n207: - **THEN** the timeout tuple SHALL be `(5.0, 120)` (connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n208: \n209: ### Requirement: Logging\n210: \n211: The system SHALL provide configurable logging for `AgentRuntimeClient` operations.\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Verbose logging enabled\n214: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with `verbose=True`\n215: - **WHEN** operations are performed\n216: - **THEN** the logger SHALL output debug-level messages\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Default logging level\n219: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with `verbose=False` (default)\n220: - **WHEN** operations are performed\n221: - **THEN** the logger SHALL output at `INFO` level or higher\n222: \n223: ## File Changes\n224: \n225: | Action | File | Description |\n226: |--------|------|-------------|\n227: | Create | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` class with context manager support |\n228: | Create | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Agent Runtime data plane |\n\n(End of file - total 228 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct an `AgentRuntimeClient` that resolves configuration from arguments and environment variables, bootstraps a session ID via the data plane, and initializes the underlying `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n\n#### Scenario: Constructor with all arguments\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is constructed with explicit `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, and `connect_timeout`\n- **WHEN** the constructor completes\n- **THEN** all instance fields (`agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `logger`, `router_url`, `session_id`) SHALL be set to the provided values\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866210530,"end":1775866210537}}}}
