{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866307310,"sessionID":"ses_2862337a6ffeds16ehO2RvNRjD","part":{"id":"prt_d79e05ec3001ytLs3ALljenFpr","messageID":"msg_d79e001fe001ZMRbmzLrmZvyOw","sessionID":"ses_2862337a6ffeds16ehO2RvNRjD","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_7dce73696e7e43ab89c009b7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-028 вҖ” SDK AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” Tasks\n\n> **Module:** sdk-python\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-028/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-028/design.md`, `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** AR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient вҖ” shared utilities, exceptions, scaffolding)\n\n---\n\n## T-1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient вҖ” Base URL and HTTP session\n\n- [ ] Verify `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` constructs `base_url` via `urljoin(router_url, f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n- [ ] Verify `SESSION_HEADER` class constant equals `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- [ ] Verify session is created via `create_session()` with `HTTPAdapter(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)`\n- [ ] Verify default `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0` are stored\n- [ ] Write test: `base_url` is correctly constructed from `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`\n- [ ] Write test: `SESSION_HEADER` equals `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n- [ ] Write test: session has `HTTPAdapter` with `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n- [ ] Write test: constructor stores all fields correctly with explicit arguments\n- [ ] Write test: constructor uses default `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_client\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-2: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient вҖ” bootstrap_session_id\n\n- [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` sends `GET` to `self.base_url`\n- [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header from response\n- [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` when header is absent\n- [ ] Verify `bootstrap_session_id()` calls `resp.raise_for_status()`\n- [ ] Write test: `bootstrap_session_id()` returns session ID when header is present\n- [ ] Write test: `bootstrap_session_id()` raises `ValueError` when header is missing\n- [ ] Write test: `bootstrap_session_id()` raises `HTTPError` on non-2xx response\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_bootstrap_session\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-3: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient вҖ” invoke\n\n- [ ] Verify `invoke(session_id, payload)` sends `POST` to `self.base_url`\n- [ ] Verify request includes header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- [ ] Verify request includes header `Content-Type: application/json`\n- [ ] Verify request body is JSON-serialized `payload`\n- [ ] Verify timeout defaults to `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` when `timeout=None`\n- [ ] Verify timeout is `(connect_timeout, timeout)` when explicit `timeout` is provided\n- [ ] Verify `invoke()` returns `requests.Response` object without parsing\n- [ ] Verify `invoke()` calls `resp.raise_for_status()`\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` POSTs correct URL with session header and JSON body\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=None` uses default read timeout `120`\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=60.0` uses read timeout `60.0`\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` returns raw `requests.Response`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_invoke\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-4: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient вҖ” close\n\n- [ ] Verify `close()` calls `self.session.close()`\n- [ ] Write test: `close()` closes the underlying HTTP session without error\n- [ ] Write test: `close()` is idempotent (safe to call multiple times)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_data_plane_close\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-5: AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” Initialization with defaults\n\n- [ ] Verify `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` stores `agent_name`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n- [ ] Verify `router_url` is resolved from arg or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n- [ ] Verify `ValueError` is raised when neither `router_url` arg nor `ROUTER_URL` env is set\n- [ ] Verify `dp_client` is constructed as `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with resolved params\n- [ ] Write test: constructor with only `agent_name` uses all defaults\n- [ ] Write test: constructor with explicit args stores all fields correctly\n- [ ] Write test: constructor resolves `router_url` from `ROUTER_URL` env var\n- [ ] Write test: constructor raises `ValueError` when no `router_url` available\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_init_defaults\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-6: AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” Session bootstrapping and reuse\n\n- [ ] Verify when `session_id=None`, constructor calls `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()` and stores result\n- [ ] Verify when `session_id` is provided, constructor does NOT call `bootstrap_session_id()`\n- [ ] Verify logger is created via `get_logger()` with `level=\"DEBUG\"` if `verbose=True`, else `\"INFO\"`\n- [ ] Write test: `session_id=None` triggers bootstrap and stores returned session ID\n- [ ] Write test: `session_id=\"existing-id\"` skips bootstrap and uses provided value\n- [ ] Write test: `verbose=True` creates logger with DEBUG level\n- [ ] Write test: `verbose=False` (default) creates logger with INFO level\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_session\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-7: AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” Context manager\n\n- [ ] Verify `__enter__()` returns `self`\n- [ ] Verify `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)` calls `close()`\n- [ ] Verify `__exit__` does NOT suppress exceptions (returns `None` or `False`)\n- [ ] Write test: `__enter__` returns `self`\n- [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with no exception calls `close()`\n- [ ] Write test: `__exit__` with exception calls `close()` and re-raises exception\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_context_manager\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-8: AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” invoke\n\n- [ ] Verify `invoke(payload)` validates `session_id` is truthy; raises `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` if falsy\n- [ ] Verify `invoke(payload)` calls `dp_client.invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)`\n- [ ] Verify `invoke(payload)` returns `resp.json()` (parsed JSON, not raw response)\n- [ ] Verify `invoke(payload, timeout=30.0)` passes `timeout=30.0` to data plane\n- [ ] Verify `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` passes `timeout=None` to data plane (data plane uses default)\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with valid session calls `dp_client.invoke()` and returns parsed JSON\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `session_id=None` raises `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=30.0` passes timeout to data plane\n- [ ] Write test: `invoke()` with `timeout=None` passes `None` to data plane\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_invoke\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-9: AgentRuntimeClient вҖ” close\n\n- [ ] Verify `close()` calls `dp_client.close()`\n- [ ] Write test: `close()` delegates to `dp_client.close()`\n- [ ] Write test: `close()` is idempotent (safe to call multiple times)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_close\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-10: Integration tests\n\n- [ ] Write integration test: full lifecycle with context manager (init вҶ’ bootstrap вҶ’ invoke вҶ’ cleanup)\n- [ ] Write integration test: pre-provisioned session skips bootstrap\n- [ ] Write integration test: invoke with custom timeout\n- [ ] Write integration test: context manager exit with exception still closes session\n- [ ] Write integration test: missing `ROUTER_URL` raises `ValueError`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_agent_runtime_integration\"`\n\n---\n\n## T-11: Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n\n- [ ] `ruff check python-sdk/agentcube/` вҖ” no violations\n- [ ] `mypy python-sdk/agentcube/` вҖ” no type errors\n- [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` вҖ” all pass\n- [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` вҖ” coverage вүҘ 80%\n\n**Verification:** Run all lint/typecheck/coverage commands\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-1 в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-2\n      в”ңв”Җв”Җ T-3\n      в””в”Җв”Җ T-4\n\nT-5 в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-6 в”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җ T-7\n      в”Ӯ         в”ңв”Җв”Җ T-8\n      в”Ӯ         в””в”Җв”Җ T-9\n      в”Ӯ\n      в””в”Җв”Җ (depends on T-1, T-2, T-3, T-4 for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient)\n\nT-10 в”Җв”Җ (T-6, T-7, T-8, T-9)\n\nT-11 в”Җв”Җ (all above)\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T-1 | None |\n| G2 | T-2, T-3, T-4 | T-1 |\n| G3 | T-5 | T-1 (AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient exists) |\n| G4 | T-6, T-7, T-8, T-9 | T-5, T-2, T-3, T-4 |\n| G5 | T-10 | T-6, T-7, T-8, T-9 |\n| G6 | T-11 | All above |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | `AgentRuntimeClient` can be imported from `agentcube` | `python -c \"from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\"` |\n| AC2 | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` can be imported from `agentcube.clients` | `python -c \"from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"` |\n| AC3 | Constructor resolves config from args and env vars | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_init_defaults\"` |\n| AC4 | Session bootstrap via GET works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_bootstrap_session\"` |\n| AC5 | Session reuse with provided `session_id` works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_session\"` |\n| AC6 | Context manager lifecycle works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_context_manager\"` |\n| AC7 | Invoke with payload and timeout works | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_invoke\"` |\n| AC8 | Invoke without session raises `ValueError` | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_invoke\"` |\n| AC9 | Close is idempotent | `pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_client_close\"` |\n| AC10 | Data plane base URL construction is correct | `p